📊 Customer Churn Analysis — Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)
🔍 Overview
This project performs a comprehensive Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on the Telco Customer Churn dataset. The goal is to understand what factors drive customers to leave a telecom company, and to surface actionable insights that could support retention strategies.
📁 Dataset

Source: Telco Customer Churn — Kaggle
Size: 7,043 customers × 21 features
Target variable: Churn (Yes / No)

🛠️ What's Inside

✅ Data cleaning & missing value imputation
📊 Univariate analysis — distributions for numerical & categorical features
📈 Churn rate (%) per category for every feature
🔗 Bivariate analysis — scatter plots colored by churn status
📦 Boxplots comparing churned vs. retained customers
🌡️ Correlation heatmap
🧪 Statistical significance tests (Chi-Square & Mann-Whitney U)

💡 Key Findings

Month-to-month contract customers churn at a much higher rate than long-term contract holders
Fiber optic internet service is associated with significantly higher churn
Customers without TechSupport or OnlineSecurity are more likely to churn
Electronic check payment method has the highest churn rate
Gender shows no significant impact on churn

🧰 Tech Stack
Python · Pandas · Plotly · SciPy · Scikit-learn · NumPy
